<paragraph id="293F36DCFFFCB966758A3066302E9A51" blockId="1.[151,502,1849,1910]" box="[151,267,1884,1910]" pageId="1" pageNumber="48">
<figureCitation id="B1BB2A59FFFCB966758A3066302E9A51" box="[151,267,1884,1910]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 13" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1899,1920]" captionTargetBox="[182,1436,188,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,156,1901]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 13. Bhatia radhamaniae sp. nov. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 2. Head and thorax, profile; 3. Face; 4. Forewing, 5. Male pygophore, lateral view; 6. Subgenital plate; 7. Male style; 8. Connective; 9. Aedeagus, lateral view; 10. Aedeagus, ventral view; 11. Female seventh sternite, ventral view; 12. Second pair of valvula, left lateral view; 13. Magnified view of teeth on second pair of valvula, left lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190679/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="48">
Figs 
<number id="9F4824FBFFFCB96675CC3066302E9A51" box="[209,267,1884,1910]" pageId="1" pageNumber="48" value="7.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="1.0">1–13</number>
</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="619A6557FFFCB964758A309330E19EF9" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="50" pageId="1" pageNumber="48" type="description">
<paragraph id="293F36DCFFFCB964758A309330009C01" blockId="1.[151,1435,1961,2026]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,152,1222]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="50" pageId="1" pageNumber="48">Pale brown with green tinge. Head olivaceous; ocelli margined by brown to dark brown; spot between inner margin of eye and ecdysial line on vertex brown; lower marginal area of face light brown. Few irregular spots on anterior margin of pronotum and scutellum pale brown. Forewing venation brown, few apical cross veins, apices of claval veins and claval apex dark brown. Pro and meso-thoracic legs with brown patches on coxae, trochanter, femur and tibiae especially on lower surface; tarsi pale greenish yellow; bases of hind tibial spines dark brown.</paragraph>
<caption id="7DFF6654FFFFB965758A305130A19AFF" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190679/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" targetBox="[182,1436,188,1898]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="293F36DCFFFFB965758A305130A19AFF" blockId="2.[151,1436,1899,2008]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="1BF4EACEFFFFB965758A305133469AA7" bold="true" box="[151,611,1899,1920]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
FIGURES 1–13. 
<taxonomicName id="EE804D5FFFFFB9657459305133359AA7" box="[324,528,1899,1920]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bhatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="radhamaniae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="1BF4EACEFFFFB9657459305133359AA7" bold="true" box="[324,528,1899,1920]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
Bhatia 
<taxonomicName id="EE804D5FFFFFB9657491305133359AA7" box="[396,528,1899,1920]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" rank="species" species="radhamaniae" status="sp. nov.">radhamaniae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="00C757B5FFFFB965770B305133469AA7" box="[534,611,1899,1920]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
1. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 2. Head and thorax, profile; 3. Face; 4. Forewing, 5. Male pygophore, lateral view; 6. Subgenital plate; 7. Male style; 8. Connective; 9. Aedeagus, lateral view; 10. Aedeagus, ventral view; 11. Female seventh sternite, ventral view; 12. Second pair of valvula, left lateral view; 13. Magnified view of teeth on second pair of valvula, left lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="293F36DCFFFEB96475DB360835749CC0" blockId="3.[151,1437,152,1222]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
Vertex medially transversely impressed, longer medially than next to eyes, about 
<number id="9F4824FBFFFEB96471D4360835FD9C6B" box="[1225,1240,306,332]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="4.0">4</number>
times as broad between eyes as median length; anterior margin with 
<number id="9F4824FBFFFEB96476043663320D9C54" box="[793,808,345,371]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="4.0">4</number>
transverse carinae dorsad of ocelli, stem of ecdysial line well-developed. Face in profile flat, with 
<number id="9F4824FBFFFEB96477CC36BA33C59CBD" box="[721,736,384,410]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="2.0">2</number>
transverse carinae ventrad of ocelli, rest shagreen. Ocelli placed 
<number id="9F4824FBFFFEB96475F1369C31DE9CE7" box="[236,251,422,448]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="2.0">2</number>
times own diameter away from adjacent eye. Pronotum in profile slightly convex, anterior margin convex. Scutellum, flat. 
<collectingCountry id="5197764CFFFEB96474A836F730D59CC0" box="[437,496,461,487]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Hind</collectingCountry>
basitarsus with 
<number id="9F4824FBFFFEB96477B036F733999CC0" box="[685,700,461,487]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="3.0">3</number>
platellae on apical transverse row.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="293F36DCFFFEB96475DB36CE325C9E3B" blockId="3.[151,1437,152,1222]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="1BF4EACEFFFEB96475DB36CE30579F2A" box="[198,370,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: Male pygophore conically rounded caudo-dorsally, with several stout setae in caudal half, without appendages or oblique ridge. Subgenital plate triangular with caudal appendage, with few marginal slender short setae, inner margin straight in proximal half. Style stout, without subapical lobe, caudally truncate, inner angle bluntly mesally produced, surface with transverse and oblique rugae. Aedeagus with well-developed broad plate at base preceding dorsal apodeme, latter bearing lateral sinuate, blade-like process with serrated distal margin in ventral view (arrowed in 
<figureCitation id="B1BB2A59FFFEB9647654358F32D09FE8" box="[841,1013,693,719]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 13" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1899,1920]" captionTargetBox="[182,1436,188,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,156,1901]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 13. Bhatia radhamaniae sp. nov. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 2. Head and thorax, profile; 3. Face; 4. Forewing, 5. Male pygophore, lateral view; 6. Subgenital plate; 7. Male style; 8. Connective; 9. Aedeagus, lateral view; 10. Aedeagus, ventral view; 11. Female seventh sternite, ventral view; 12. Second pair of valvula, left lateral view; 13. Magnified view of teeth on second pair of valvula, left lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190679/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
Figs 
<number id="9F4824FBFFFEB964769B358F32B09FE8" box="[902,917,693,719]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="9.0">9</number>
and 
<number id="9F4824FBFFFEB96476CE358F32D09FE8" box="[979,1013,693,719]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
); shaft cylindrical, half as long as posterior processes, with large gonopore opening on posterior surface apically; with pair of posterior long caudally diverging slender processes arising near base of shaft.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="293F36DCFFFEB96475DB3413300B9EB7" blockId="3.[151,1437,152,1222]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="1BF4EACEFFFEB96475DB341330AB9E65" box="[198,398,809,834]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Female genitalia</emphasis>
: Seventh sternum broader than long, medially produced into bilobed projection. Second pair of valvulae with anterior tubercle, cutting edge 
<number id="9F4824FBFFFEB964762B346A327B9E4D" box="[822,862,848,874]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="0.4">0.4</number>
as long as total length, teeth prominent with crenulations.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="293F36DCFFFEB96475DB34A730E19EF9" blockId="3.[151,1437,152,1222]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="1BF4EACEFFFEB96475DB34A730559E91" box="[198,368,925,950]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Measurements</emphasis>
: Male 
<quantity id="EE789B39FFFEB96474DB34A733709E90" box="[454,597,925,951]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.4" metricValueMax="6.7" metricValueMin="6.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="6.4" valueMax="6.7" valueMin="6.1">6.1–6.7 mm</quantity>
long and 2.0– 
<quantity id="EE789B39FFFEB964761E34A732789E90" box="[771,861,925,951]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes. Female 
<quantity id="EE789B39FFFEB964718034A734099E90" box="[1181,1324,925,951]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.25" metricValueMax="8.3" metricValueMin="8.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="8.25" valueMax="8.3" valueMin="8.2">8.2–8.3 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity id="EE789B39FFFEB964758A34FE31D49EF9" box="[151,241,964,990]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
